Introduction

Wumuti is a Uyghur-Chinese singer. He is the leader of the boy group XLOV, a member of the project boy group WATERFIRE, and a former member of the Chinese boy group SWIN and its sub-unit SWIN-S. He left the group and the company in 2018.

He debuted as a soloist under JPARK&COMPANY on January 16th, 2023, with a song called "seOUL" in collaboration with fellow Under Nineteen contestant, Rose.

He is best known for being a contestant on the Chinese survival show Super Idol, Korean survival shows Under Nineteen (left the show), Boys Planet (eliminated in episode 8), and Build Up (eliminated in episode 10).

On December 17, 2024, it was revealed that he would be debuting in a group named XLOV.
